rovide a qualitatively similar chromospheric field,\nwhere the azimuth of the former is better aligned with Ca ii 8542 {\\AA} fibrils\nthan that of the WFA, especially outside strong-field concentrations. The\namount of structure as well as the transverse field strengths are\nunderestimated by the MHS extrapolation. This underscores the importance of\nconsidering a chromospheric magnetic field constraint in data-driven modelling\nof active regions.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 7 Sep 2021 08:51:44 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-06-22"}
